725943f-c.title: Queens: 162nd Street - Jamaica Avenue
725943f-c.text:
162nd St. (formerly 24-26 Union Ave.) east side, north of Jamaica
Ave., showing in a set of 4 views the Hewlett Creed Tavern. This
building was moved in 1858 when Union Ave. was extended into this ares.
Other occupants were the Bonnie Briar Tea Room in 1924 and the
Roosevelt Restaurant in 1934. The building was rased in 1934.
1922
Views 1 and 2.
Views 3 and 4:March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726985f-b.text:

Streets, showing (left to right) the Register's Office building,

Company Building (nine stories), and the Title Guarantee and Trust

Place.
